#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn12.64"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.64:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.64:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.64:0.3"
msgid "64. Atthirāgasutta "
msgstr "64. If There Is Desire "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.101, sc1
msgctxt "sn12.64:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.64:1.2"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ vā anuggahāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four fuels. They maintain sentient beings that have been born and help those that are about to be born. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:1.3"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn12.64:1.4"
msgid "Kabaḷīkāro āhāro oḷāriko vā sukhumo vā, phasso dutiyo, manosañcetanā tatiyā, viññāṇaṃ catutthaṃ. "
msgstr "Solid food, whether coarse or fine; contact is the second, mental intention the third, and consciousness the fourth. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:1.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro āhārā bhūtānaṃ vā sattānaṃ ṭhitiyā sambhavesīnaṃ vā anuggahāya. "
msgstr "These are the four fuels that maintain sentient beings that have been born and help those that are about to be born. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn12.64:2.1"
msgid "Kabaḷīkāre ce, bhikkhave, āhāre atthi rāgo atthi nandī atthi taṇhā, patiṭṭhitaṃ tattha viññāṇaṃ virūḷhaṃ. "
msgstr "If there is desire, relishing, and craving for solid food, consciousness becomes established there and grows. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:2.2"
msgid "Yattha patiṭṭhitaṃ viññāṇaṃ virūḷhaṃ, atthi tattha nāmarūpassa avakkanti. "
msgstr "Where consciousness is established and grows, name and form are conceived. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:2.3"
msgid "Yattha atthi nāmarūpassa avakkanti, atthi tattha saṅkhārānaṃ vuddhi. "
msgstr "Where name and form are conceived, there is the growth of choices. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:2.4"
msgid "Yattha atthi saṅkhārānaṃ vuddhi, atthi tattha āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti. "
msgstr "Where choices grow, there is rebirth into a new state of existence in the future. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:2.5"
msgid "Yattha atthi āyatiṃ punabbhavābhinibbatti, atthi tattha āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Where there is rebirth into a new state of existence in the future, there is rebirth, old age, and death in the future. "

msgctxt "sn12.64:2.6"
msgid "Yattha atthi āyatiṃ jātijarāmaraṇaṃ, sasokaṃ taṃ, bhikkhave, sadaraṃ saupāyāsanti vadāmi. "
msgstr "Where there is rebirth, old age, and death in the future, I say this is full of sorrow, anguish, and distress. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn12.64:3.1"
msgid "Phasse ce, bhikkhave, āhāre … pe … "
msgstr "If there is desire, relishing, and craving for contact as fuel … "

msgctxt "sn12.64:3.2"
msgid "manosañcetanāya ce, bhikkhave, āhāre … "
msgstr "If there is desire, relishing, and craving for mental intention as fuel … "

msgctxt "sn12.64:3.3"
msgid "viññāṇe ce, bhikkhave, āhāre atthi rāgo atthi nandī atthi taṇhā, patiṭṭhitaṃ tattha viññāṇaṃ virūḷhaṃ. "
msgstr "If there is desire, relishing, and craving for consciousness as fuel, consciousness becomes established there and grows. "

